</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-151_ pf-text-1"><strong>Microlearning</strong> - Delivering bite-sized learning modules that are focused, concise, and easily digestible, typically lasting no longer than 10 minutes.
</li><li data-pf-type="List2.Item2" class="sc-fXEqDS gMGtOR pf-153_ pf-text-1"><strong>Gamification</strong> - Incorporating game elements, such as points, badges, and leaderboards, into learning experiences to increase engagement and motivation.
</li></ul><h3 data-pf-type="Heading2" class="sc-dtMgUX gYEGeC pf-155_ pf-heading-1-h3">Personalised learning
</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-157_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">Personalised learning is expected to continue gaining traction in 2024, as organisations recognise the importance of catering to the unique needs and preferences of learners. By leveraging data analytics and artificial intelligence, organisations can deliver customised learning experiences that are tailored to each learner's skill level, learning pace, and interests. This approach not only enhances engagement but also improves learning outcomes by ensuring that learners receive content that is relevant and meaningful to them.
