</h3><p class="sc-cZMNgc hqfPHB pf-168_ pf-text-1" data-pf-type="Paragraph3">In an age of information overload, microlearning offers a solution by providing learners with short, focused learning modules that can be consumed on-the-go. With attention spans dwindling, microlearning allows learners to access content in convenient, bite-sized chunks, making it easier to retain information and apply it in real-world scenarios. In 2024, we can expect to see increased adoption of microlearning across industries as organisations seek to deliver learning experiences that are engaging, efficient, and effective.
